# API Service Checklist

## Router
- Keep endpoints RESTful and resource-oriented; prefer plural nouns and kebab-case paths.
- Version all HTTP APIs under `/api/v1`.
- Register routes by feature and keep router definitions thin.

## Handler
- Define request/response DTOs at the handler boundary.
- Validate path/query/body params in handler before calling services.
- Map domain/service errors to stable HTTP status codes and messages.
- Avoid business logic in handlers.

## Services
- Implement services with action-based structure (`CreateXService`, `StartXService`, etc.).
- Expose one action per service via `Execute(...)`.
- Keep shared constants, errors, and shared contracts in `common`/`contracts`.
- Keep persistence and domain transitions in services, not in handlers.

## Testing
- Add unit tests for router/handler mappings (auth, validation, status mapping).
- Add unit tests for service behavior (happy path + key failure branches).
- Update tests when route naming or response contracts change.
